node.text: It’s a well known fact that winged eyeliner is notoriously hard to achieve, but make-up artist @RaoulAlejandre and @PoppyDelevingne are here to provide you with the insider tricks you need. In the latest #MakeUpMasters episode with #BritishVogue, watch as the pair take on the classic Hollywood look using the new make-up line from @Valentino.Beauty. You’ll be achieving winged eyeliner like #SophiaLoren in no time.

node.text: Amy Jackson has built her wardrobe around pre-loved pieces. Looking for clothes that give her the “feel-good factor”, the actor and model knows how to spot a glamorous vintage piece – including a dress previously owned by #PrincessMargaret. From celebrating renowned designers like @StellaMcCartney with an item that is “happiness in a jumper”, to championing new designers like @ClioPeppiatt, watch as Amy talks us through her seven favourite looks.

node.text: As the Olympic spirit sweeps the nation, let former Olympic gymnast Emilie Goldblum guide you through a restorative #WorkoutWednesday. From competing in the 2000 Summer Games in Sydney to performing with #Cher and #TheWeeknd, Emilie has done it all, so she’s no stranger to looking after her body to avoid injuries. Join in as she takes you through a 20 minute stretch session, and tag @BritishVogue in your next #WorkoutWednesday video to let us know where you're taking part.

Racing down LA’s Melrose Avenue in the California sun, supermodel #AlessandraAmbrosio takes on Vogue’s latest Shopping Challenge. The goal? She must style three animal-print outfits for three occasions, in just 60 minutes. Watch as she embraces her wild side as she styles a selection of looks for a brunch, job interview and party. 

This episode of The Shopping Challenge was filmed pre-pandemic and before social distancing guidelines were issued.

node.text: It’s a well-known fact that wearing SPF is one of the best ways to protect your skin – but how do you do it right to avoid signs of ageing and pigmentation? Watch as #BritishVogue’s beauty and lifestyle director @JessicaDiner does a sunscreen deep dive with @LaRochePosay dermatologist Dr Hiva Fassihi to discuss how to incorporate SPF into your everyday make-up routine (and why make-up with SPF isn’t enough), the difference between the effects of ultraviolet A and ultraviolet B on your skin, and why it’s important to apply sunscreen even if you’re not leaving the house.

node.title: Face Facts: The Importance Of SPF No Matter The Season

node.text: It’s a well known fact that winged eyeliner is notoriously hard to achieve, but make-up artist @RaoulAlejandre and @PoppyDelevingne are here to provide you with the insider tricks you need. In the latest #MakeUpMasters episode with #BritishVogue, watch as the pair take on the classic Hollywood look using the new make-up line from @Valentino.Beauty. You’ll be achieving winged eyeliner like #SophiaLoren in no time.

node.text: When the Taliban began taking control of large swathes of Afghanistan in May, internally displaced persons began flooding into Kabul, only for the capital to fall in turn on 15 August. As the world reckons with the resulting humanitarian crisis, click the link in bio for photographs taken on the ground, and a list of charities and organisations to donate to now.

node.text:
How to combat the most Monday-ish Monday? @Kristen_McMenamy’s Instagram account. 
At 56, McMenamy is still as exuberant, stylish, and provocative as she was when she made her name as the face of @Chanel and @Versace in the late ’80s and early ’90s. And while she might only have joined Instagram as recently as April, her 30,000 followers make up a who’s who of fashion, from #NaomiCampbell to #MarcJacobs and many, many more. Click the link in bio for more on your new favourite follow.

The first time that @Madonna graced the cover of #BritishVogue was over 30 years ago, shortly after her thirtieth birthday, and just before she released #LikeAPrayer. At the link in bio, revisit the interview from the February 1989 issue, in which a 30-Year-Old Madonna reveals the “real” her.

#Madonna photographed by Herb Ritts and styled by Sarajane Hoare for the February 1989 issue of British Vogue.

node.text: "When a woman frees herself from the colour bottle, chances are she will not go back. I know I never did!" While once we scrambled to cover any sort of silver, white or grey hair, this is no longer the case – instead, it’s never been chicer. At the link in bio, eight women share their stories about going grey, along with products they love and why it's the most empowering beauty choice one can make.

node.text:
Who says a white wedding gown is your only option? Founder of @Tat.London, @The.Charlie.P married her boyfriend of 10 years in her “fantasy” fuchsia @CarolinaHerrera dress. After rearranging her wedding three times, “Everything else had fallen away… I just wanted to have my best friend become my husband,” she writes. Click the link in bio to read Charlie’s account of the colourful day in full.

Photographed by @WillPatrickWeddings.

node.text: Ahead of the #SexAndTheCity reboot, writer Deborah Linton reflects on the way a best friendship in her 30s changed the course of her life. “The depiction, over six seasons and two movies, of four ostensibly different women, who found their way into the chapters of one another’s lives just when they were needed there, reflects all that I have learned to be true about the friendships that fulfil us most: they may well be among the great loves of our life.” Read her essay in full, at the link in bio.
